    "# Mini-Project 02 — End-to-End Phylogenetics Pipeline on Real Data\n",
    "\n",
    "**Module:** 08 — Bioinformatics: Sequence Analysis  \n",
    "**Notebook:** 17 of 18 (Portfolio artifact 2)  \n",
    "**Time estimate:** 4–6 hours  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Portfolio artifact:** `portfolio/module08_phylogenetics_pipeline/`\n",
    "\n",
    "> This is the Track A and B portfolio centerpiece for Module 08.\n",
    "> An end-to-end, reproducible, documented pipeline: NCBI → MAFFT → distances → NJ → figure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Pipeline overview\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "1. Fetch sequences from NCBI (Biopython Entrez)\n",
    "        ↓\n",
    "2. Write to FASTA (datasets/raw/betoglobin_raw.fasta)\n",
    "        ↓\n",
    "3. Align with MAFFT (external tool)\n",
    "   mafft --auto datasets/raw/betoglobin_raw.fasta > datasets/processed/betoglobin_aligned.fasta\n",
    "        ↓\n",
    "4. Compute JC69 and K2P distance matrices (from scratch)\n",
    "        ↓\n",
    "5. Build NJ tree from distance matrix (from scratch)\n",
    "        ↓\n",
    "6. Produce portfolio figure (4-panel)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Reproducibility contract:** This notebook must run from scratch given only:\n",
    "- Internet access (for NCBI)\n",
    "- MAFFT installed and on PATH\n",
    "- This notebook"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 1 — Fetch sequences from NCBI\n",
    "\n",
    "Dataset: beta-globin gene family (HBB gene) from 5 species.\n",
    "These sequences are well-studied and the expected phylogeny is known."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from Bio import Entrez, SeqIO\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "Entrez.email = 'your.email@example.com'  # Replace with your email\n",
    "\n",
    "# Accession numbers for beta-globin mRNA\n",
    "accessions = {\n",
    "    'Human':    'NM_000518',  # Homo sapiens HBB\n",
    "    'Chimp':    'XM_001172049', # Pan troglodytes\n",
    "    'Gorilla':  'XM_019019628', # Gorilla gorilla\n",
    "    'Mouse':    'NM_008220',  # Mus musculus Hbb-b1\n",
    "    'Zebrafish': 'NM_001020522', # Danio rerio hbba1\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "os.makedirs('../datasets/raw', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "os.makedirs('../datasets/processed', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "records = []\n",
    "for species, acc in accessions.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Fetching {species} ({acc})...\")\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        handle = Entrez.efetch(\n",
    "            db='nucleotide', id=acc, rettype='fasta', retmode='text'\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        record = SeqIO.read(handle, 'fasta')\n",
    "        record.id = species\n",
    "        record.description = f'{species} beta-globin {acc}'\n",
    "        records.append(record)\n",
    "        print(f\"  Fetched: {len(record.seq)} bp\")\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"  Error: {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "raw_fasta = '../datasets/raw/betoglobin_raw.fasta'\n",
    "SeqIO.write(records, raw_fasta, 'fasta')\n",
    "print(f\"\\nWrote {len(records)} sequences to {raw_fasta}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 2 — Align with MAFFT\n",
    "\n",
    "**Install MAFFT:** `conda install -c bioconda mafft`  \n",
    "**Document the exact command and version used — required for reproducibility.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check MAFFT version\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    result = subprocess.run(['mafft', '--version'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n",
    "    print('MAFFT version:', result.stderr.strip() or result.stdout.strip())\n",
    "except FileNotFoundError:\n",
    "    print('MAFFT not found. Install with: conda install -c bioconda mafft')\n",
    "    print('Skipping alignment step (using pre-aligned data if available)')\n",
    "\n",
    "aligned_fasta = '../datasets/processed/betoglobin_aligned.fasta'\n",
    "mafft_cmd = f'mafft --auto {raw_fasta}'\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCommand: {mafft_cmd}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Output: {aligned_fasta}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run MAFFT\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    with open(aligned_fasta, 'w') as f:\n",
    "        result = subprocess.run(\n",
    "            ['mafft', '--auto', raw_fasta],\n",
    "            stdout=f, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    print('MAFFT alignment complete.')\n",
    "    print('Stderr:', result.stderr[:200] if result.stderr else 'None')\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f'MAFFT failed: {e}')\n",
    "    print('Using synthetic aligned sequences for demonstration...')\n",
    "    # Fallback: synthetic pre-aligned sequences\n",
    "    aligned_seqs = {\n",
    "        'Human':     'ATGGTGCACCTGACTCCTGAGGAGAAGTCTGCCGTTACTGCCCTGTGGGGCAAGGTGAACGTGGATGAAGTTGGTGG',\n",
    "        'Chimp':     'ATGGTGCACCTGACTCCTGAGGAGAAGTCTGCCGTTACTGCCCTGTGGGGCAAGGTGAACGTGGATGAAGTTGGTGG',\n",
    "        'Gorilla':   'ATGGTGCACCTGACTCCTGAGGAGAAGTCTGCCGTTACTGCCCTGTGGGGCAAGGTGAACGTGGATGAAGTTGGTGG',\n",
    "        'Mouse':     'ATGGTGCATCTGTCCAGTGAGGAGAAGTCTGCGGTCACTGCCCTGTGGGGCAAGGTGAATGTGGATGAAGTTGGTGG',\n",
    "        'Zebrafish': 'ATGGTGCACTGGACTGCTGAGGAGAAGCAGGTCGCCATTGCCACAATGGGCAAGGTAAATGTGGATGAAGTGGGAGG',\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    from Bio.SeqRecord import SeqRecord\n",
    "    from Bio.Seq import Seq\n",
    "    aligned_records = [SeqRecord(Seq(v), id=k, description='') for k, v in aligned_seqs.items()]\n",
    "    SeqIO.write(aligned_records, aligned_fasta, 'fasta')\n",
    "    print('Wrote synthetic aligned sequences.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 3 — Load alignment and compute distance matrix\n",
    "import math\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "aligned_records = list(SeqIO.parse(aligned_fasta, 'fasta'))\n",
    "aligned_seqs = {r.id: str(r.seq).upper() for r in aligned_records}\n",
    "species_names = list(aligned_seqs.keys())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(aligned_seqs)} aligned sequences:\")\n",
    "for sp, seq in aligned_seqs.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {sp}: {len(seq)} bp\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def observed_p(seq1: str, seq2: str) -> float:\n",
    "    total, diffs = 0, 0\n",
    "    for a, b in zip(seq1, seq2):\n",
    "        if '-' in (a, b): continue\n",
    "        total += 1\n",
    "        if a != b: diffs += 1\n",
    "    return diffs / total if total > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def jc_distance(seq1: str, seq2: str) -> float:\n",
    "    p = observed_p(seq1, seq2)\n",
    "    if p >= 0.75: return float('inf')\n",
    "    return -0.75 * math.log(1 - 4*p/3)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "n = len(species_names)\n",
    "D = np.zeros((n, n))\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    for j in range(i+1, n):\n",
    "        d = jc_distance(aligned_seqs[species_names[i]], aligned_seqs[species_names[j]])\n",
    "        D[i, j] = d\n",
    "        D[j, i] = d\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nJC69 Distance Matrix:\")\n",
    "max_name = max(len(n) for n in species_names)\n",
    "print(' ' * max_name + '  ' + '  '.join(f'{n:>10}' for n in species_names))\n",
    "for i, sp in enumerate(species_names):\n",
    "    row = f'{sp:<{max_name}}  ' + '  '.join(f'{D[i,j]:>10.4f}' for j in range(n))\n",
    "    print(row)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save\n",
    "import csv\n",
    "csv_path = '../datasets/processed/distance_matrix.csv'\n",
    "with open(csv_path, 'w', newline='') as f:\n",
    "    writer = csv.writer(f)\n",
    "    writer.writerow([''] + species_names)\n",
    "    for i, sp in enumerate(species_names):\n",
    "        writer.writerow([sp] + list(D[i]))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDistance matrix saved to {csv_path}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 4 — Build NJ tree from scratch\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "from typing import Optional\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class NJNode:\n",
    "    name: str\n",
    "    left: Optional['NJNode'] = None\n",
    "    right: Optional['NJNode'] = None\n",
    "    left_dist: float = 0.0\n",
    "    right_dist: float = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "    def is_leaf(self): return self.left is None\n",
    "\n",
    "    def to_newick(self) -> str:\n",
    "        if self.is_leaf(): return self.name\n",
    "        return f'({self.left.to_newick()}:{self.left_dist:.5f},{self.right.to_newick()}:{self.right_dist:.5f})'\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def neighbour_joining(dist_matrix: np.ndarray, names: list) -> NJNode:\n",
    "    n_orig = len(names)\n",
    "    max_nodes = 2 * n_orig\n",
    "    big_D = np.zeros((max_nodes, max_nodes))\n",
    "    big_D[:n_orig, :n_orig] = dist_matrix.copy()\n",
    "    D = big_D\n",
    "    nodes = [NJNode(name=name) for name in names] + [None] * (max_nodes - n_orig)\n",
    "    active = list(range(n_orig))\n",
    "    next_idx = n_orig\n",
    "\n",
    "    while len(active) > 2:\n",
    "        n = len(active)\n",
    "        row_sum = {i: sum(D[i, j] for j in active if j != i) for i in active}\n",
    "        min_q = float('inf')\n",
    "        min_i, min_j = -1, -1\n",
    "        for a in range(len(active)):\n",
    "            for b in range(a+1, len(active)):\n",
    "                i, j = active[a], active[b]\n",
    "                q = (n-2)*D[i,j] - row_sum[i] - row_sum[j]\n",
    "                if q < min_q: min_q = q; min_i, min_j = i, j\n",
    "\n",
    "        d_ij = D[min_i, min_j]\n",
    "        bi = d_ij/2 + (row_sum[min_i]-row_sum[min_j])/(2*(n-2)) if n > 2 else d_ij/2\n",
    "        bj = d_ij - bi\n",
    "        bi, bj = max(0.0, bi), max(0.0, bj)\n",
    "\n",
    "        nodes[next_idx] = NJNode('', nodes[min_i], nodes[min_j], bi, bj)\n",
    "        for k in active:\n",
    "            if k in (min_i, min_j): continue\n",
    "            nd = (D[min_i,k] + D[min_j,k] - d_ij) / 2\n",
    "            D[next_idx,k] = D[k,next_idx] = nd\n",
    "\n",
    "        active.remove(min_i); active.remove(min_j); active.append(next_idx)\n",
    "        next_idx += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    i, j = active\n",
    "    return NJNode('root', nodes[i], nodes[j],\n",
    "                  max(0, D[i,j]/2), max(0, D[i,j]/2))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "nj_tree = neighbour_joining(D, species_names)\n",
    "newick = nj_tree.to_newick() + ';'\n",
    "print(\"NJ Tree (Newick):\")\n",
    "print(newick)\n",
    "\n",
    "newick_path = '../datasets/processed/nj_tree.newick'\n",
    "with open(newick_path, 'w') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(newick + '\\n')\n",
    "print(f\"\\nNewick tree saved to {newick_path}\")"
   ]
  },
